problem_statement:
[ðŸ› Bug]: waitForDisplayed command leaks
### Have you read the Contributing Guidelines on issues?

- [x] I have read the [Contributing Guidelines on issues](https://github.com/webdriverio/webdriverio/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md#reporting-new-issues).

### WebdriverIO Version

9.10.1

### Node.js Version

v20.18.2

### Mode

Standalone Mode

### Which capabilities are you using?

```typescript
{
  browserName: "chrome",
  "goog:chromeOptions": {
    args: ["--headless=new", "--disable-gpu"],
  },
  "wdio:enforceWebDriverClassic": true,
}
```

### What happened?

When running `waitForDisplayed({ reverse: true })`, there are leaking interval checks even after the session is closed

### What is your expected behavior?

There are no leaks

### How to reproduce the bug.

Put this into a sample project for convenience: https://github.com/just-boris/wdio-leaking-wait

Webdriver code

```js
import { remote } from "webdriverio";

const browser = await remote({
  logLevel: "info",
  capabilities: {
    browserName: "chrome",
    "goog:chromeOptions": {
      args: ["--headless=new", "--disable-gpu"],
    },
    // without this capability the waitForDisplayed does not work at all
    "wdio:enforceWebDriverClassic": true,
  },
});

await browser.url("http://localhost:8080");

await browser.saveScreenshot("before.png");
try {
  await browser.$(".loading").waitForDisplayed({ reverse: true });
} finally {
  await browser.saveScreenshot("after.png");
  await browser.deleteSession();
}
```

HTML file

```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />

    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
<div class="loading">Loading...</div>
<script>
    setTimeout(() => {
        document.querySelector('.loading').remove();

        const container = document.createElement('div');
        container.textContent = 'Ready!';
        document.body.appendChild(container);
    }, 500);
</script>
</body>
</html>

```

